{
  "texts": [
    "Hidden states (s) in the model, which were inferred based on observations, were also categorical and included a heartbeat state, a no heartbeat state, and a \"start\" state.",
    "Each trial in the model corresponded to a window in the EKG time series in which either a systole or diastole signal was present.",
    "Each trial formally had two timesteps (t = 1 and t = 2).",
    "At t = 1, the participant always formally began in the \"start\" state and made the associated \"start\" observation.",
    "At t = 2, the participant either observed a systole or a diastole and inferred whether they had transitioned from the \"start\" state into the heartbeat state or the no heartbeat state."
  ]
}